01:10.912 --> 01:12.079
What are you thinking about?

01:12.097 --> 01:14.431
You look beautiful.

01:14.466 --> 01:16.383
Thank you.

01:16.417 --> 01:17.918
What are you thinking?

01:17.936 --> 01:19.853
That your furniture's
really old.

01:19.888 --> 01:22.856
I think the word you're
looking for is "antiquey."

01:22.891 --> 01:26.393
That is not a word, and
this sofa is Ikea circa 1994.

01:26.427 --> 01:27.778
Okay, I get it.

01:27.812 --> 01:30.281
So you get up early just so you
can do a thorough critiquing

01:30.315 --> 01:31.615
of my furniture?

01:31.650 --> 01:35.486
Actually, I got up early,
so I could figure out

01:35.537 --> 01:39.039
if there's anything around here
that I could stand living with.

01:41.793 --> 01:44.111
Ah...I'm sorry--do you want
to move in together?

01:44.129 --> 01:45.829
Yeah, I mean,
if the offer still stands.

01:45.880 --> 01:49.333
Are you kidding me?

01:49.384 --> 01:50.801
So is that a yes?

01:50.835 --> 01:53.754
Oh, no, this is a yes.

01:58.459 --> 02:00.144
I figured out
what we can bring.

02:00.178 --> 02:01.512
- What?
- You.

02:01.563 --> 02:03.347
Panda, right here.

02:03.398 --> 02:05.099
That's my favorite piece of art.

02:05.133 --> 02:07.151
That is not art.

02:07.185 --> 02:08.969
Grammy gave that to me.

02:08.987 --> 02:10.104
Oh, I love it.
Panda can come.

02:10.138 --> 02:11.105
And the chair.

02:11.139 --> 02:12.740
Oh.

02:12.774 --> 02:13.741
That was
Grammy's favorite chair.

02:13.775 --> 02:14.975
I don't--I don't--

02:14.993 --> 02:16.643
No, no, no, no, no,
I'm telling you, Rachel,

02:16.661 --> 02:19.813
she used to sit in that chair
every Sunday

02:19.831 --> 02:22.649
and drink her hot cup
of Hershey's cocoa

02:22.667 --> 02:25.002
and tell me
all about growing up

02:25.036 --> 02:27.320
on the mean streets
of Philadelphia.

02:27.339 --> 02:30.157
When you lie,
try less details.

02:30.175 --> 02:31.158
Got it.

02:42.670 --> 02:44.638
Looking for me?

02:44.672 --> 02:47.174
No.

02:47.192 --> 02:50.177
The woman I'm looking for
is a lot more in my bed.

02:50.195 --> 02:53.313
What can I say?
My schedule stops for no man.

02:53.347 --> 02:57.534
Yes, but we've got
a little unfinished...

02:57.569 --> 03:00.120
Business.

03:00.155 --> 03:02.623
I wouldn't call last night
"unfinished."

03:02.657 --> 03:05.659
And I wouldn't call it
"business."

03:09.581 --> 03:12.532
I was talking about breakfast.

03:12.550 --> 03:14.501
Harvey Specter
makes breakfast?

03:14.535 --> 03:16.003
You never heard
of the Specter special?

03:16.037 --> 03:17.805
I think I just had
the Specter special.

03:17.839 --> 03:18.806
Oh, no, no, no, no.

03:18.840 --> 03:20.924
The Specter special is--
Let me guess.

03:20.975 --> 03:24.895
It's two eggs, over easy,

03:24.929 --> 03:28.148
with a side of "Scottie,
I want you in my life."

03:28.183 --> 03:29.566
Bacon.

03:29.601 --> 03:31.935
And now I'm reconsidering
the "in my life" thing.

03:31.986 --> 03:35.072
Oh, no, I saw your face.
You had your serious face on.

03:35.106 --> 03:37.491
"Scottie, I want you
in my life.

03:37.525 --> 03:40.611
Scottie...
I want you in my life."

03:40.662 --> 03:43.363
You know what?
You don't deserve my bacon.

03:43.397 --> 03:46.733
Oh, that's fine,
'cause I have to go anyway.

03:46.751 --> 03:48.202
Where could you have to go?
You're unemployed.

03:48.236 --> 03:51.071
Well, actually a top-tier
law firm offered me a job

03:51.089 --> 03:52.539
last night,
and I thought it might be best

03:52.573 --> 03:54.541
if I negotiate the terms
of my agreement

03:54.575 --> 03:57.511
with the partner
I'm not sleeping with.

03:57.545 --> 04:00.914
There's a slight problem
with that plan.

04:03.301 --> 04:05.385
You offered her a job
before talking to me?

04:05.419 --> 04:08.555
I didn't offer her a job.
I asked her if she wanted one.

04:08.589 --> 04:11.108
I didn't want to waste
your time, and for the record,

04:11.142 --> 04:12.182
we'd be lucky to have her.

04:12.193 --> 04:13.527
I know that.

04:13.561 --> 04:15.395
But my question isn't
why I should want her here,

04:15.429 --> 04:16.779
it's why you would want
her here.

04:16.815 --> 04:20.567
She's the best lawyer I know,
after me.

04:20.601 --> 04:21.767
And you.

04:21.786 --> 04:22.986
Are you sleeping with her?

04:23.037 --> 04:24.538
Excuse me?

04:24.572 --> 04:26.156
You have history
with this woman,

04:26.207 --> 04:27.541
so I just want to know

04:27.575 --> 04:29.376
are you doing this
because you feel sorry for her

04:29.410 --> 04:30.494
or because you want to pay
her back

04:30.545 --> 04:31.962
or because you love her
or what?

04:31.996 --> 04:33.964
- It's none of your business.
- It is my business.

04:33.998 --> 04:36.250
It is literally my business.

04:39.304 --> 04:41.805
I want a relationship
with her.

04:41.840 --> 04:42.973
Well, I'm happy for you.

04:43.007 --> 04:45.125
I hope you two make a run at it.
Thanks.

04:45.143 --> 04:46.626
I'll pretend you meant that.

04:46.644 --> 04:48.262
Your track record
isn't great.

04:48.296 --> 04:50.297
You've had three name partners
in two years.

04:50.315 --> 04:51.798
Let's talk
about your commitment issues.

04:51.816 --> 04:52.933
I'm not asking you

04:52.967 --> 04:55.402
to give my commitment issues
a corner office.

04:55.436 --> 04:56.937
You don't need to give her
a corner office.

04:56.971 --> 04:58.238
Any regular office will do.

04:58.273 --> 05:00.440
Harvey, I get it.

05:00.474 --> 05:03.476
She's a catch, for you
and for this firm.

05:03.495 --> 05:05.015
But what happens
when you two break up?

05:05.029 --> 05:07.281
Who says
we're gonna break up?

05:10.651 --> 05:14.321
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

05:14.339 --> 05:17.657
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

